==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kneipp cure
<hw>Kneipp cure</hw></mhw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>,
<def>Treatment of disease by forms of hydrotherapy, as walking barefoot
in the morning dew, baths, wet compresses, cold affusions, etc.; -- so
called from its originator, <person>Sebastian
<etsep>Kneipp</etsep></person> (1821-97), a German priest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Knell</ent>⟦br⟧
